"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-kaylia-nemour-uneven-bars-routine-beloved-simone-biles-fans\", \"text\": \"17-year-old Algerian gymnast Kaylia Nemour soared to a gold medal finish during Sunday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s uneven bars final after an absolutely captivating individual performance.\\u00c2  Nemour scored a whopping 15.7 to win her first ever gold medal and become the first Olympic medalist in gymnastics from Africa. She defeated reigning world champion, China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Qiu Qiyuan (15.5), who took home silver, and American gymnast Sunisa Lee, who took home bronze.  Among those watching at Bercy Arena was Simone Biles, who was no doubt in the house to cheer on her compatriot, Lee.  But even Biles couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t contain her excitement after seeing Nemour flawlessly stick the landing and raise both her arms in the air. Nemour immediately teared up on the mat, knowing she delivered possibly the best routine of her young Olympic career.  Biles was seen applauding Nemour's performance with a wide smile on her face. Nemour and Lee also shared a sweet embrace after Nemour\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s score was announced.\\u00c2  Algeria\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Kaylia Nemour put on one of her best performances in the uneven bars final to win gold, and Simone Biles loved it. \\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u0087#ParisOlympicspic.twitter.com/iXDorLBrRW  The Algerian breakout star finished fifth in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s all-around final earlier this week but convincingly earned her spot on the podium on Sunday with a stunning show that left fans breathless.  People were especially happy for Nemour to win while representing Algeria, instead of France. Nemour holds dual citizenship in both countries but chose to compete for Algeria this summer due to areporteddispute between the French gymnastics federation and her club, Avoine Beaumont.  OH MY. \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u00b2What a stellar uneven bars routine from Algeria\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Kaylia Nemour!#ParisOlympics\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00ba NBC and Peacockpic.twitter.com/gZPZkZ0MFd  france did everything to block kaylia from switching to algeria and qualifying to the olympics \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 SHE JUST WON THE OLYMPIC GOLD MEDAL SAY HER NAME !!!!!pic.twitter.com/PMHFPaByZO  15.700 POUR KAYLIA NEMOUR. OH KAYLIA TU ES MAGNIFIQUE \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u00ad\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00a9\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00bfpic.twitter.com/oKYZuftFFX  kaylia nemour is gonna get a gold medal for algeria in her home country of france after everything that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s happened with the federation\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6. absolutely poetic  Kaylia Nemour winning ub gold IN france on the 20th anniversary of France\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s one and only wag olympic medal after they continually screwed her over, this is the best day of my life!!!pic.twitter.com/niZkniwaov  No one swings like Kaylia Nemour. No one.  Kristen Wong is a staff writer on the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated. She has been a sports journalist since 2020. Before joining SI in November 2023, Wong covered four NFL teams as an associate editor with the FanSided NFL Network and worked as a staff writer for the brand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s flagship site. Outside of work, she has dreams of running her own sporty dive bar.  Follow kriscwong  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2025ABG-SI LLC- SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"